+- [Recommendations](#-recommendations)
+- [Summary](#-summary)
+- [References](#-references)
+
+---
+
+## 📌 Overview: What Is `axios`?
+
+`axios` is a widely adopted **HTTP client library** for JavaScript, used in both **Node.js** and **browser-based** applications. It is commonly used to:
+
+- Communicate with external APIs
+- Perform server-to-server HTTP requests
+- Handle authentication headers and tokens
+- Implement request and response interceptors
+
+Because axios is often responsible for **network communication and credential handling**, it is frequently flagged by security scanners and treated as a high-risk dependency.
+
+---
+
+## ⚠️ Why SNYK-JS-AXIOS-6124857 Is Reported
+
+Security scanners report **SNYK-JS-AXIOS-6124857** based on:
+
+- Static vulnerability metadata
+- Version-based matching rules
+- Advisory data that does not evaluate actual source history
+
+As a result, scanners flag **axios v1.11.0** without verifying whether the **upstream fix is already present** in the version.
+
+---
+
+## ✅ Why This Issue Is Already Fixed
+
+The issue described in **SNYK-JS-AXIOS-6124857** is **not present** in axios v1.11.0.
+
+Key facts:
+
+- The issue was **fixed upstream in axios**
+- The fix was released **before axios v1.11.0**
+- axios v1.11.0 includes all upstream fixes by default
+
+**Conclusion:**  
+The installed version is **already secure**, and no remediation is required.
+
+---
+
+## 🔍 Fix Lineage and Proof
+
+### 🔹 Upstream Fix Inclusion
+
+- The fix associated with **SNYK-JS-AXIOS-6124857** was merged into axios **prior to v1.11.0**
+- axios v1.11.0 is a **newer release** that includes this fix as part of its normal release history
+- There are **no missing commits, regressions, or reversions** related to this issue in v1.11.0
+
+This confirms that the vulnerable code path **does not exist** in the installed version.
+
+---
+
+## ❗ Why This Is a False Positive
+
+This finding is a **false positive** because:
+
+- The scanner uses **coarse-grained version matching**
+- Commit ancestry and release history are not evaluated
+- axios v1.11.0 is incorrectly flagged despite being fixed
+
+The report reflects a **tooling limitation**, not a real vulnerability.
+
+---
+
+## 💥 Why You Must NOT Patch This Manually
+
+Manually patching axios for this issue is **incorrect and unnecessary**:
+
+- ✅ The fix is already included
+- ❌ Reapplying fixes can introduce instability
+- ❌ Backporting fixed logic risks breaking expected behavior
+- ❌ Manual changes invalidate dependency integrity and audits
+
+There is **nothing to patch**.
+
+---
+
+## ✅ Recommendations
+
+- ✅ Mark **SNYK-JS-AXIOS-6124857** as **FALSE POSITIVE**
+- ✅ Do not apply any patches or backports
+- ✅ Continue using axios v1.11.0 or later
+- 📝 Document this justification for audit purposes
+- 🔄 Continue standard dependency monitoring
+
+---
+
+## 🧷 Summary
+
+- **SNYK-JS-AXIOS-6124857 is already fixed**
+- axios v1.11.0 includes the required fix
+- The scanner result is a **false positive**
+- No remediation action is required
+
